## Standards
- Every tool must have a docstring â€” NanoBot uses it for tool selection
- Input schemas use Zod (TS) or Pydantic (Python) â€” no `any` types
- Tool names: `snake_case`, max 40 chars, prefixed by namespace (`searxng_`, `bird_`, `memory_`)
- Return type: always `{ content: [{ type: "text", text: string }] }` for MCP compatibility
- Errors: raise/throw â€” never return error strings (MCP handles error propagation)
- `toolTimeout` in NanoBot config must match your expected SLA + 10s buffer

## Adding a New MCP Tool
1. Add tool registration in relevant route file in `mcp-bridge/src/tools/`
2. Export from `mcp-bridge/src/index.ts`
3. Add entry to `~/.nanobot/config.json` â†’ `tools.mcpServers`
4. Restart `nanobot-gateway`: `docker compose restart nanobot-gateway`
5. Verify: `nanobot agent -m "List your available tools"` â€” new tool should appear
